Ukrainian enters airport on fake ticket to see off friend.
New Delhi, Jul 26 (PTI) A Ukraine national has been apprehended for entering the Indira Gandhi International airport terminal allegedly using a fake ticket. He was apprehended yesterday around 11 am when the Central Industrial Security Force personnel, deployed for the airports security, found him roaming suspiciously inside the terminal building, a senior official in airport security said today. The man was identified as Ukranie national S Podbolotnyy. He told the CISF personnel that he had come to see off his woman friend, who was travelling to Almaty, the official said. 